collectAio(uint256).details: User must approve this contract beforehand. Pulls AIO via safeTransferFrom, then immediately forwards entire amount to projectWallet.Protected by nonReentrant to prevent reentrancy attacks.

params.amount: Amount of AIO tokens to collect

collectErc20(address,uint256).details: User must approve this contract beforehand. Pulls tokens via safeTransferFrom, then immediately forwards entire amount to projectWallet.Protected by nonReentrant to prevent reentrancy attacks.

collectEth().details: Requires msg.value >= feeWei. Forwards entire msg.value to projectWallet.Protected by nonReentrant to prevent reentrancy attacks.

collectUsdt(uint256).details: User must approve this contract beforehand. Pulls USDT via safeTransferFrom, then immediately forwards entire amount to projectWallet.Protected by nonReentrant to prevent reentrancy attacks.

params.feeWei_: Minimum ETH fee per interaction (e.g., 1e15 = 0.001 ETH)
params.owner_: Address that will own the contract
params.projectWallet_: Address that will receive all fees (EOA or Safe multisig)

enableGovernanceMode(address,address).details: Only callable once by owner or trustedBootstrapper. After enabling, owner renounces control to timelock/admin.

params.paramSetter: Address that can set parameters (will receive PARAM_SETTER_ROLE)
params.timelock: TimelockController or Safe multisig address (will receive DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE)

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

setAioToken(address).details: Only callable by owner or PARAM_SETTER_ROLE (if governance mode enabled)

setFeeWei(uint256).details: Only callable by owner or PARAM_SETTER_ROLE (if governance mode enabled)

setProjectWallet(address).details: Only callable by owner or PARAM_SETTER_ROLE (if governance mode enabled)

setTrustedBootstrapper(address).details: Only callable by owner before governance mode is enabled

params.bootstrapper: Address of the trusted bootstrapper contract

setUsdtToken(address).details: Only callable by owner or PARAM_SETTER_ROLE (if governance mode enabled)

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

PARAM_SETTER_ROLE().notice: Role for setting parameters (fee, wallet, etc.)

collectAio(uint256).notice: Collects AIO token fee from the caller

collectErc20(address,uint256).notice: Collects ERC20 token fee from the caller (generic method)

collectEth().notice: Collects ETH fee from the caller

collectUsdt(uint256).notice: Collects USDT fee from the caller

enableGovernanceMode(address,address).notice: Enables governance mode with timelock and parameter setter role

feeWei().notice: Minimum ETH fee per interaction (in wei)

projectWallet().notice: Project wallet address that receives all fees

trustedBootstrapper().notice: Optional trusted bootstrapper address that can call enableGovernanceMode
